{
  "texts": [
    "Several participants described having to work with scanned documents which may or may not have had OCR applied to them.",
    "In the case of materials scientists, many often consulted technical reports from the 1950s to 70s that were originally typewritten; some of our policy experts looked at digitized government documents that were hand-scanned.",
    "Even in cases where documents had been produced digi-tally, understanding rich visual content, like page layouts, tables, and charts was a key area of focus for nearly all of our participants.",
    "Local context tasks.",
    "Local context tasks, which only involve the content of a single document, resemble common information extraction tasks."
  ]
}